title: Dodecagram
summary: In geometry, a dodecagram (from Greek  δώδεκα (dṓdeka) 'twelve', and  γραμμῆς (grammēs) 'line'[1]) is a star polygon or compound with 12 vertices. There is one regular dodecagram polygon (with Schläfli symbol {12/5}  and a turning number of 5). There are also 4 regular compounds {12/2}, {12/3}, {12/4}, and {12/6}.
